        <briefdescription>
<para>Runtime (non-literal) format-string helper for ICEBERG_LOG_RUNTIME_FMT. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>std::format requires a compile-time format string; this routes a runtime string through std::vformat. Args are bound as named lvalues and the arg-store is held in a named variable so it outlives the vformat call (C++23 make_format_args rejects rvalues <ndash/> P2905 / LWG3631). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
